In the past, I've used [[DNS]] based [[Access Controls]], but it was occasionally problematic. I'm now using NCSA basic authentication.

### Squid Configuration
<pre class="sh_sh">
auth_param basic program /usr/lib/squid3/ncsa_auth /etc/squid3/acls/users
auth_param basic children 5
auth_param basic realm Squid proxy-caching web server
auth_param basic credentialsttl 2 hours
auth_param basic casesensitive off
</pre>

<pre class="sh_sh">
acl ncsa_users proxy_auth REQUIRED
http_access allow ncsa_users
</pre>

### Password File Creation

Just like for [[Apache]]:

<pre class="sh_sh">
htpasswd -c /etc/squid3/acls/users
</pre>

